FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of underlying InstrumentPartySubID (1053) value.Same values as PartySubIDType (803) Valid values: 1 - Firm 2 - Person 3 - System 4 - Application 5 - Full legal name of firm 6 - Postal address 7 - Phone number 8 - Email address 9 - Contact name 10 - Securities account number (for settlement instructions) 11 - Registration number (for settlement instructions and confirmations) 12 - Registered address (for confirmation purposes) 13 - Regulatory status (for confirmation purposes) 14 - Registration name (for settlement instructions) 15 - Cash account number (for settlement instructions) 16 - BIC 17 - CSD participant member code 18 - Registered address 19 - Fund account name 20 - Telex number 21 - Fax number 22 - Securities account name 23 - Cash account name 24 - Department 25 - Location desk 26 - Position account type 27 - Security locate ID 28 - Market maker 29 - Eligible counterparty 30 - Professional client 31 - Location 32 - Execution venue 33 - Currency delivery identifier

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidSwapPoints
FixFieldSpec.Description: The bid FX Swap points for an FX Swap. It is the "far bid forward points - near offer forward point". Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

FixFieldSpec.Name: OfferSwapPoints
FixFieldSpec.Description: The offer FX Swap points for an FX Swap. It is the "far offer forward points - near bid forward points". Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegBidForwardPoints
FixFieldSpec.Description: The bid FX forward points for the leg of an FX Swap. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegOfferForwardPoints
FixFieldSpec.Description: The offer FX forward points for the leg of an FX Swap. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

FixFieldSpec.Name: SwapPoints
FixFieldSpec.Description: For FX Swap, this is used to express the differential between the far leg's bid/offer and the near leg's bid/offer. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDQuoteType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies market data quote type. Valid values: 0 - Indicative 1 - Tradeable 2 - Restricted Tradeable 3 - Counter 4 - Indicative and Tradeable

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastSwapPoints
FixFieldSpec.Description: For FX Swap, this is used to express the last market event for the differential between the far leg's bid/offer and the near leg's bid/offer in a fill or partial fill. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

FixFieldSpec.Name: SideGrossTradeAmt
FixFieldSpec.Description: The gross trade amount for this side of the trade. See also GrossTradeAmt (381) for additional definition.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegLastForwardPoints
FixFieldSpec.Description: The forward points for this leg's fill event. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegCalculatedCcyLastQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used for the calculated quantity of the other side of the currency for this leg. Can be derived from LegQty and LegLastPx.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegGrossTradeAmt
FixFieldSpec.Description: The gross trade amount of the leg. For FX Futures this is used to express the notional value of a fill when LegLastQty and other quantity fields are express in terms of contract size.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MaturityTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Time of security's maturity expressed in local time with offset to UTC specified

FixFieldSpec.Name: RefOrderID
FixFieldSpec.Description: The ID reference to the order being hit or taken

FixFieldSpec.Name: RefOrderIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to specify what identifier, provided in order depth market data, to use when hitting (taking) a specific order. Valid values: 4 - Original order ID 0 - SecondaryOrderID(198) 1 - OrderID(37) 2 - MDEntryID(278) 3 - QuoteEntryID(299)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecondaryDisplayQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used for reserve orders when DisplayQty applies to the primary execution market (e.g.an ECN) and another quantity is to be shown at other markets (e.g. the exchange). On orders specifies the qty to be displayed, on execution reports the currently displayed quantity.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DisplayWhen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Instructs when to refresh DisplayQty (1138). Valid values: 1 - Immediate (after each fill) 2 - Exhaust (when DisplayQty = 0)

FixFieldSpec.Name: DisplayMethod
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines what value to use in DisplayQty (1138). If not specified the default DisplayMethod is "1" Valid values: 4 - Undisclosed (invisible order) 1 - Initial (use original DisplayQty) 2 - New (use RefreshQty) 3 - Random (randomize value)

FixFieldSpec.Name: DisplayLowQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the lower quantity limit to a randomized refresh of DisplayQty.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DisplayHighQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the upper quantity limit to a randomized refresh of DisplayQty.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DisplayMinIncr
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the minimum increment to be used when calculating a random refresh of DisplayQty. A user specifies this when he wants a larger increment than the standard provided by the market (e.g. the round lot size).

FixFieldSpec.Name: RefreshQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the quantity used to refresh DisplayQty.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MatchIncrement
FixFieldSpec.Description: Allows orders to specify a minimum quantity that applies to every execution (one execution could be for multiple counter-orders). The order may still fill against smaller orders, but the cumulative quantity of the execution must be in multiples of the MatchIncrement.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MaxPriceLevels
FixFieldSpec.Description: Allows an order to specify a maximum number of price levels to trade through. Only valid for aggressive orders and during continuous (autoexecution) trading sessions. Property lost when order is put on book. A partially filled order is assigned last trade price as limit price. Non-filled order behaves as ordinary Market or Limit.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PreTradeAnonymity
FixFieldSpec.Description: Allows trader to explicitly request anonymity or disclosure in pre-trade market data feeds. Anonymity is relevant in markets where counterparties are regularly disclosed in order depth feeds. Disclosure is relevant when counterparties are not normally visible.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PriceProtectionScope
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the type of price protection the customer requires on their order. Valid values: 0 - None 1 - Local (Exchange, ECN, ATS) 2 - National (Across all national markets) 3 - Global (Across all markets)

FixFieldSpec.Name: LotType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the lot type assigned to the order. Valid values: 1 - Odd Lot 2 - Round Lot 3 - Block Lot 4 - Round lot based upon UnitOfMeasure(996)

FixFieldSpec.Name: PegPriceType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the type of peg. Valid values: 1 - Last peg (last sale) 2 - Mid-price peg (midprice of inside quote) 3 - Opening peg 4 - Market peg 5 - Primary peg (primary market - buy at bid or sell at offer) 7 - Peg to VWAP 8 - Trailing Stop Peg 9 - Peg to Limit Price

FixFieldSpec.Name: PeggedRefPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: The value of the reference price that the order is pegged to. PeggedRefPrice + PegOffsetValue (211) = PeggedPrice (839) unless the limit price (44, Price) is breached. The values may not be exact due to rounding.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PegSecurityIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the identity of the security off whose prices the order will peg. Same values as SecurityIDSource (22) Valid values: 1 - CUSIP 2 - SEDOL 3 - QUIK 4 - ISIN number 5 - RIC code 6 - ISO Currency Code 7 - ISO Country Code 8 - Exchange Symbol 9 - Consolidated Tape Association (CTA) Symbol (SIAC CTS/CQS line format) A - Bloomberg Symbol B - Wertpapier C - Dutch D - Valoren E - Sicovam F - Belgian G - "Common" (Clearstream and Euroclear) H - Clearing House / Clearing Organization I - ISDA/FpML Product Specification (XML in EncodedSecurityDesc) J - Option Price Reporting Authority K - ISDA/FpML Product URL (URL in SecurityID) L - Letter of Credit M - Marketplace-assigned Identifier

FixFieldSpec.Name: PegSecurityID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the identity of the security off whose prices the order will peg.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PegSymbol
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the common, 'human understood' representation of the security off whose prices the order will Peg.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PegSecurityDesc
FixFieldSpec.Description: Security description of the security off whose prices the order will Peg.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines when the trigger will hit, i.e. the action specified by the trigger instructions will come into effect. Valid values: 1 - Partial Execution 2 - Specified Trading Session 3 - Next Auction 4 - Price Movement

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerAction
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the type of action to take when the trigger hits. Valid values: 1 - Activate 2 - Modify 3 - Cancel

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: The price at which the trigger should hit.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerSymbol
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the common, 'human understood' representation of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerSecurityID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the identity of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerSecurityIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the identity of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic. Same values as SecurityIDSource (22). Valid values: 1 - CUSIP 2 - SEDOL 3 - QUIK 4 - ISIN number 5 - RIC code 6 - ISO Currency Code 7 - ISO Country Code 8 - Exchange Symbol 9 - Consolidated Tape Association (CTA) Symbol (SIAC CTS/CQS line format) A - Bloomberg Symbol B - Wertpapier C - Dutch D - Valoren E - Sicovam F - Belgian G - "Common" (Clearstream and Euroclear) H - Clearing House / Clearing Organization I - ISDA/FpML Product Specification (XML in EncodedSecurityDesc) J - Option Price Reporting Authority K - ISDA/FpML Product URL (URL in SecurityID) L - Letter of Credit M - Marketplace-assigned Identifier

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerSecurityDesc
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the security description of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerPriceType
FixFieldSpec.Description: The type of price that the trigger is compared to. Valid values: 1 - Best Offer 2 - Last Trade 3 - Best Bid 4 - Best Bid or Last Trade 5 - Best Offer or Last Trade 6 - Best Mid

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerPriceTypeScope
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the type of price protection the customer requires on their order. Valid values: 0 - None 1 - Local (Exchange, ECN, ATS) 2 - National (Across all national markets) 3 - Global (Across all markets)

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerPriceDirection
FixFieldSpec.Description: The side from which the trigger price is reached. Valid values: U - Trigger if the price of the specified type goes UP to or through the specified Trigger Price. D - Trigger if the price of the specified type goes DOWN to or through the specified Trigger Price.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerNewPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: The Price that the order should have after the trigger has hit. Could be applicable for any trigger type, but must be specified for Trigger Type 1.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerOrderType
FixFieldSpec.Description: The OrdType the order should have after the trigger has hit. Required to express orders that change from Limit to Market. Other values from OrdType (40) may be used if appropriate and bilaterally agreed upon. Valid values: 1 - Market 2 - Limit

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerNewQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: The Quantity the order should have after the trigger has hit.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerTradingSessionID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the trading session at which the order will be activated.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TriggerTradingSessionSubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the subordinate trading session at which the order will be activated.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrderCategory
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the type of interest behind a trade (fill or partial fill). Valid values: 1 - Order 2 - Quote 3 - Privately Negotiated Trade 4 - Multileg order 5 - Linked order 6 - Quote Request 7 - Implied Order 8 - Cross Order 9 - Streaming price (quote)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoRootPartyIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of RootPartyID (1117), RootPartyIDSource (1118), and RootPartyRole (1119) entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: RootPartyID
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyID value within a root parties component. Same values as PartyID (448)

FixFieldSpec.Name: RootPartyIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyIDSource value within a root parties component. Same values as PartyIDSource (447) Valid values:For all PartyRoles B - BIC (Bank Identification Code - SWIFT managed) code (ISO9362 - See "Appendix 6-B") C - Generally accepted market participant identifier (e.g. NASD mnemonic) D - Proprietary / Custom code E - ISO Country Code F - Settlement Entity Location (note if Local Market Settlement use "E=ISO Country Code") (see "Appendix 6-G" for valid values) G - MIC (ISO 10383 - Market Identificer Code) (See "Appendix 6-C") H - CSD participant/member code (e.g.. Euroclear, DTC, CREST or Kassenverein number)For PartyRole = "InvestorID" and for CIV 6 - UK National Insurance or Pension Number 7 - US Social Security Number 8 - US Employer or Tax ID Number 9 - Australian Business Number A - Australian Tax File NumberFor PartyRole = "InvestorID" and for Equities 1 - Korean Investor ID 2 - Taiwanese Qualified Foreign Investor ID QFII/FID 3 - Taiwanese Trading Acct 4 - Malaysian Central Depository (MCD) number 5 - Chinese Investor IDFor PartyRole="Broker of Credit" I - Directed broker three character acronym as defined in ISITC "ETC Best Practice" guidelines document

FixFieldSpec.Name: RootPartyRole
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyRole value within a root parties component. Same values as PartyRole (452) Valid values: 82 - Central Registration Depository (CRD) 83 - Clearing Account 84 - Acceptable Settling Counterparty 85 - Unacceptable Settling Counterparty 1 - Executing Firm (formerly FIX 4.2 ExecBroker) 2 - Broker of Credit (formerly FIX 4.2 BrokerOfCredit) 3 - Client ID (formerly FIX 4.2 ClientID) 4 - Clearing Firm (formerly FIX 4.2 ClearingFirm) 5 - Investor ID 6 - Introducing Firm 7 - Entering Firm 8 - Locate / Lending Firm (for short-sales) 9 - Fund Manager Client ID (for CIV) 10 - Settlement Location (formerly FIX 4.2 SettlLocation) 11 - Order Origination Trader (associated with Order Origination Firm - i.e. trader who initiates/submits the order) 12 - Executing Trader (associated with Executing Firm - actually executes) 13 - Order Origination Firm (e.g. buy-side firm) 14 - Giveup Clearing Firm (firm to which trade is given up) 15 - Correspondant Clearing Firm 16 - Executing System 17 - Contra Firm 18 - Contra Clearing Firm 19 - Sponsoring Firm 20 - Underlying Contra Firm 21 - Clearing Organization 22 - Exchange 24 - Customer Account 25 - Correspondent Clearing Organization 26 - Correspondent Broker 27 - Buyer/Seller (Receiver/Deliverer) 28 - Custodian 29 - Intermediary 30 - Agent 31 - Sub-custodian 32 - Beneficiary 33 - Interested party 34 - Regulatory body 35 - Liquidity provider 36 - Entering trader 37 - Contra trader 38 - Position account 39 - Contra Investor ID 40 - Transfer to Firm 41 - Contra Position Account 42 - Contra Exchange 43 - Internal Carry Account 44 - Order Entry Operator ID 45 - Secondary Account Number 46 - Foreign Firm 47 - Third Party Allocation Firm 48 - Claiming Account 49 - Asset Manager 50 - Pledgor Account 51 - Pledgee Account 52 - Large Trader Reportable Account 53 - Trader mnemonic 54 - Sender Location 55 - Session ID 56 - Acceptable Counterparty 57 - Unacceptable Counterparty 58 - Entering Unit 59 - Executing Unit 60 - Introducing Broker 61 - Quote originator 62 - Report originator 63 - Systematic internaliser (SI) 64 - Multilateral Trading Facility (MTF) 65 - Regulated Market (RM) 66 - Market Maker 67 - Investment Firm 68 - Host Competent Authority (Host CA) 69 - Home Competent Authority (Home CA) 70 - Competent Authority of the most relevant market in terms of liquidity (CAL) 71 - Competent Authority of the Transaction (Execution) Venue (CATV) 72 - Reporting intermediary (medium/vendor via which report has been published) 73 - Execution Venue 74 - Market data entry originator 75 - Location ID 76 - Desk ID 77 - Market data market 78 - Allocation Entity 79 - Prime Broker providing General Trade Services 80 - Step-Out Firm (Prime Broker) 81 - BrokerClearingID

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoRootPartySubIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of RootPartySubID (1121) and RootPartySubIDType (1122) entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: RootPartySubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartySubID value within a root parties component. Same values as PartySubID (523)

FixFieldSpec.Name: RootPartySubIDType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of RootPartySubID (1121) value. Same values as PartySubIDType (803) Valid values: 1 - Firm 2 - Person 3 - System 4 - Application 5 - Full legal name of firm 6 - Postal address 7 - Phone number 8 - Email address 9 - Contact name 10 - Securities account number (for settlement instructions) 11 - Registration number (for settlement instructions and confirmations) 12 - Registered address (for confirmation purposes) 13 - Regulatory status (for confirmation purposes) 14 - Registration name (for settlement instructions) 15 - Cash account number (for settlement instructions) 16 - BIC 17 - CSD participant member code 18 - Registered address 19 - Fund account name 20 - Telex number 21 - Fax number 22 - Securities account name 23 - Cash account name 24 - Department 25 - Location desk 26 - Position account type 27 - Security locate ID 28 - Market maker 29 - Eligible counterparty 30 - Professional client 31 - Location 32 - Execution venue 33 - Currency delivery identifier

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeHandlingInstr
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specified how the Trade Capture Report should be handled by the Respondent. Valid values: 0 - Trade Confirmation 1 - Two-Party Report 2 - One-Party Report for Matching 3 - One-Party Report for Pass Through 4 - Automated Floor Order Routing 5 - Two Party Report for Claim

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrigTradeHandlingInstr
FixFieldSpec.Description: Optionally used with TradeHandlingInstr = 0 to relay the trade handling instruction used when reporting the trade to the marketplace. Same values as TradeHandlingInstr (1123) Valid values: 0 - Trade Confirmation 1 - Two-Party Report 2 - One-Party Report for Matching 3 - One-Party Report for Pass Through 4 - Automated Floor Order Routing 5 - Two Party Report for Claim

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrigTradeDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to preserve original trade date when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrigTradeID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to preserve original trade id when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrigSecondaryTradeID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to preserve original secondary trade id when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

FixFieldSpec.Name: ApplVerID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the service pack release being applied at message level. Enumerated field with values assigned at time of service pack release Valid values: 9 - FIX50SP2 0 - FIX27 1 - FIX30 2 - FIX40 3 - FIX41 4 - FIX42 5 - FIX43 6 - FIX44 7 - FIX50 8 - FIX50SP1

FixFieldSpec.Name: CstmApplVerID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies a custom extension to a message being applied at the message level. Enumerated field

FixFieldSpec.Name: RefApplVerID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the service pack release being applied to a message at the session level. Enumerated field with values assigned at time of service pack release. Uses same values as ApplVerID Valid values: 9 - FIX50SP2 0 - FIX27 1 - FIX30 2 - FIX40 3 - FIX41 4 - FIX42 5 - FIX43 6 - FIX44 7 - FIX50 8 - FIX50SP1

FixFieldSpec.Name: RefCstmApplVerID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies a custom extension to a message being applied at the session level.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TZTransactTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Transact time in the local date-time stamp with a TZ offset to UTC identified

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExDestinationIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: The ID source of ExDestination Valid values: B - BIC (Bank Identification Code) (ISO 9362) C - Generally accepted market participant identifier (e.g. NASD mnemonic) D - Proprietary / Custom code E - ISO Country Code G - MIC (ISO 10383 - Market Identifier Code)

FixFieldSpec.Name: ReportedPxDiff
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates that the reported price that is different from the market price. The price difference should be stated by using field 828 TrdType and, if required, field 829 TrdSubType

FixFieldSpec.Name: RptSys
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the system or medium on which the report has been published

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocClearingFeeIndicator
FixFieldSpec.Description: ClearingFeeIndicator(635) for Allocation, see ClearingFeeIndicator(635) for permitted values.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DefaultApplVerID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the service pack release being applied, by default, to message at the session level. Enumerated field with values assigned at time of service pack release. Uses same values as ApplVerID Valid values: 9 - FIX50SP2 0 - FIX27 1 - FIX30 2 - FIX40 3 - FIX41 4 - FIX42 5 - FIX43 6 - FIX44 7 - FIX50 8 - FIX50SP1

FixFieldSpec.Name: DisplayQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: The quantity to be displayed . Required for reserve orders. On orders specifies the qty to be displayed, on execution reports the currently displayed quantity.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExchangeSpecialInstructions
FixFieldSpec.Description: Free format text string related to exchange.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MaxTradeVol
FixFieldSpec.Description: The maximum order quantity that can be submitted for a security.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoMDFeedTypes
FixFieldSpec.Description: The number of feed types and corresponding book depths associated with a security

FixFieldSpec.Name: MatchAlgorithm
FixFieldSpec.Description: The types of algorithm used to match orders in a specific security. Possilbe value types are FIFO, Allocation, Pro-rata, Lead Market Maker, Currency Calender.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MaxPriceVariation
FixFieldSpec.Description: The maximum price variation of an execution from one event to the next for a given security.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ImpliedMarketIndicator
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates that an implied market should be created for either the legs of a multi-leg instrument (Implied-in) or for the multi-leg instrument based on the existence of the legs (Implied-out). Determination as to whether implied markets should be created is generally done at the level of the multi-leg instrument. Commonly used in listed derivatives. Valid values: 0 - Not implied 1 - Implied-in - The existence of a multi-leg instrument is implied by the legs of that instrument 2 - Implied-out - The existence of the underlying legs are implied by the multi-leg instrument 3 - Both Implied-in and Implied-out

FixFieldSpec.Name: EventTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specific time of event. To be used in combination with EventDate [866]

FixFieldSpec.Name: MinPriceIncrementAmount
FixFieldSpec.Description: Minimum price increment amount associated with the MinPriceIncrement ( tag 969). For listed derivatives, the value can be calculated by multiplying MinPriceIncrement by ContractValueFactor(231).

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnitOfMeasureQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to indicate the quantity of the underlying commodity unit of measure on which the contract is based, such as, 2500 lbs of lean cattle, 1000 barrels of crude oil, 1000 bushels of corn, etc. UnitOfMeasureQty is required for UnitOfMeasure(996) Variable Quantity UOMs enumerations. Refer to the definition of UnitOfMeasure(996) for more information on the use of UnitOfMeasureQty.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LowLimitPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Allowable low limit price for the trading day. A key parameter in validating order price. Used as the lower band for validating order prices. Orders submitted with prices below the lower limit will be rejected

FixFieldSpec.Name: HighLimitPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Allowable high limit price for the trading day. A key parameter in validating order price. Used as the upper band for validating order prices. Orders submitted with prices above the upper limit will be rejected

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradingReferencePrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference price for the current trading price range usually representing the mid price between the HighLimitPrice and LowLimitPrice. The value may be the settlement price or closing price of the prior trading day.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityGroup
FixFieldSpec.Description: An exchange specific name assigned to a group of related securities which may be concurrently affected by market events and actions.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegNumber
FixFieldSpec.Description: Allow sequencing of Legs for a Strategy to be captured

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlementCycleNo
FixFieldSpec.Description: Settlement cycle in which the settlement obligation was generated

FixFieldSpec.Name: SideCurrency
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to identify the trading currency on the Trade Capture Report Side

FixFieldSpec.Name: SideSettlCurrency
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to identify the settlement currency on the Trade Capture Report Side

FixFieldSpec.Name: ApplExtID
FixFieldSpec.Description: The extension pack number associated with an application message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CcyAmt
FixFieldSpec.Description: Net flow of Currency 1

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoSettlDetails
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to group Each Settlement Party

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlObligMode
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to identify the reporting mode of the settlement obligation which is either preliminary or final Valid values: 1 - Preliminary 2 - Final

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlObligMsgID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Message identifier for Settlement Obligation Report

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlObligID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique ID for this settlement instruction.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlObligTransType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Transaction Type - required except where SettlInstMode is 5=Reject SSI request Valid values: C - Cancel N - New R - Replace T - Restate

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlObligRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Required where SettlInstTransType is Cancel or Replace

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlObligSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to identify whether these delivery instructions are for the buyside or the sellside. Valid values: 1 - Instructions of Broker 2 - Instructions for Institution 3 - Investor

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoSettlOblig
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of settlement obligations

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteMsgID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for a quote message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteEntryStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the status of an individual quote. See also QuoteStatus(297) which is used for single Quotes. Valid values: 0 - Accepted 5 - Rejected 6 - Removed from Market 7 - Expired 12 - Locked Market Warning 13 - Cross Market Warning 14 - Canceled due to Lock Market 15 - Canceled due to Cross Market 16 - Active

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotNoCxldQuotes
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the number of canceled quotes

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotNoAccQuotes
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the number of accepted quotes

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotNoRejQuotes
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the number of rejected quotes

FixFieldSpec.Name: PrivateQuote
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies whether a quote is public, i.e. available to the market, or private, i.e. available to a specified counterparty only. Valid values: Y - Private Quote N - Public Quote

FixFieldSpec.Name: RespondentType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the type of respondents requested. Valid values: 1 - All market participants 2 - Specified market participants 3 - All Market Makers 4 - Primary Market Maker(s)

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDSubBookType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Describes a class of sub book, e.g. for the separation of various lot types. The Sub Book Type indicates that the following Market Data Entries belong to a non-integrated Sub Book. Whenever provided the Sub Book must be used together with MDPriceLevel and MDEntryPositionNo in order to sort the order properly.Values are bilaterally agreed.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityTradingEvent
FixFieldSpec.Description:
Identifies an event related to a SecurityTradingStatus(326). An event occurs and is gone, it is not a state that applies for a period of time. Valid values: 1 - Order imbalance, auction is extended 2 - Trading resumes (after Halt) 3 - Price Volatility Interruption 4 - Change of Trading Session 5 - Change of Trading Subsession 6 - Change of Security Trading Status 7 - Change of Book Type 8 - Change of Market Depth
or any value conforming to the data type Reserved100Plus

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoStatsIndicators
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of statistics indicator repeating group entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: StatsType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of statistics Valid values: 1 - Exchange Last 2 - High / Low Price 3 - Average Price (VWAP, TWAP ... ) 4 - Turnover (Price * Qty)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoOfSecSizes
FixFieldSpec.Description: The number of secondary sizes specifies in this entry

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDSecSizeType
FixFieldSpec.Description:
Specifies the type of secondary size. Valid values: 1 - Customer
or any value conforming to the data type Reserved100Plus

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDSecSize
FixFieldSpec.Description: A part of the MDEntrySize(271) that represents secondary interest as specified by MDSecSizeType(1178).

FixFieldSpec.Name: ApplID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the application with which a message is associated. Used only if application sequencing is in effect.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ApplSeqNum
FixFieldSpec.Description: Data sequence number to be used when FIX session is not in effect

FixFieldSpec.Name: ApplBegSeqNum
FixFieldSpec.Description: Beginning range of application sequence numbers

FixFieldSpec.Name: ApplEndSeqNum
FixFieldSpec.Description: Ending range of application sequence numbers

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityXMLLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Lenght of the SecurityXML data block.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityXML
FixFieldSpec.Description: Actual XML data stream describing a security, normally FpML.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityXMLSchema
FixFieldSpec.Description: The schema used to validate the contents of SecurityXML

FixFieldSpec.Name: RefreshIndicator
FixFieldSpec.Description: Set by the sender to tell the receiver to perform an immediate refresh of the book due to disruptions in the accompanying real-time feed'Y' - Mandatory refresh by all participants'N' - Process as required

FixFieldSpec.Name: Volatility

Suspend T - Fixed Peg to Local best bid or offer at time of order ( Deprecated in FIX.5.0 ) U - Customer Display Instruction (Rule 11Ac1-1/4) V - Netting (for Forex) W - Peg to VWAP ( Deprecated in FIX.5.0 ) X - FixFieldSpec.Name: DerivativeFlowScheduleType
FixFieldSpec.Description:
The industry standard flow schedule by which electricity or natural gas is traded. Schedules exist by regions and on-peak and off-peak status, such as "Western Peak". Valid values: 0 - NERC Eastern Off-Peak 1 - NERC Western Off-Peak 2 - NERC Calendar-All Days in month 3 - NERC Eastern Peak 4 - NERC Western Peak
or any value conforming to the data type Reserved100Plus

FixFieldSpec.Name: FillLiquidityInd
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicator to identify whether this fill was a result of a liquidity provider providing or liquidity taker taking the liquidity. Applicable only for OrdStatus of Partial or Filled Valid values: 1 - Added Liquidity 2 - Removed Liquidity 3 - Liquidity Routed Out 4 - Auction

FixFieldSpec.Name: SideLiquidityInd
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicator to identify whether this fill was a result of a liquidity provider providing or liquidity taker taking the liquidity. Applicable only for OrdStatus of Partial or Filled. Valid values: 1 - Added Liquidity 2 - Removed Liquidity 3 - Liquidity Routed Out 4 - Auction

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoRateSources
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of rate sources being specified.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RateSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the source of rate information.For FX, the reference source to be used for the FX spot rate. Valid values: 0 - Bloomberg 1 - Reuters 2 - Telerate 99 - Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: RateSourceType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether the rate source specified is a primary or secondary source. Valid values: 0 - Primary 1 - Secondary

FixFieldSpec.Name: ReferencePage
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the reference "page" from the rate source.For FX, the reference page to the spot rate to be used for the reference FX spot rate.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RestructuringType
FixFieldSpec.Description: A category of CDS credit even in which the underlying bond experiences a restructuring.Used to define a CDS instrument. Valid values: FR - Full Restructuring MR - Modified Restructuring MM - Modified Mod Restructuring XR - No Restructuring specified

FixFieldSpec.Name: Seniority
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies which issue (underlying bond) will receive payment priority in the event of a default.Used to define a CDS instrument. Valid values: SD - Senior Secured SR - Senior SB - Subordinated

FixFieldSpec.Name: NotionalPercentageOutstanding
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the notional percentage of the deal that is still outstanding based on the remaining components of the index.Used to calculate the true value of a CDS trade or position.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OriginalNotionalPercentageOutstanding
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to reflect the Original value prior to the application of a credit event. See NotionalPercentageOutstanding(1451).

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingRestructuringType
FixFieldSpec.Description: See RestructuringType(1449) Valid values: FR - Full Restructuring MR - Modified Restructuring MM - Modified Mod Restructuring XR - No Restructuring specified

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingSeniority
FixFieldSpec.Description: See Seniority(1450) Valid values: SD - Senior Secured SR - Senior SB - Subordinated

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingNotionalPercentageOutstanding
FixFieldSpec.Description: See NotionalPercentageOutstanding(1451)

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingOriginalNotionalPercentageOutstanding
FixFieldSpec.Description: See OriginalNotionalPercentageOutstanding(1452)

FixFieldSpec.Name: AttachmentPoint
FixFieldSpec.Description: Lower bound percentage of the loss that the tranche can endure.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DetachmentPoint
FixFieldSpec.Description: Upper bound percentage of the loss the tranche can endure.

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingAttachmentPoint
FixFieldSpec.Description: See AttachmentPoint(1457).

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingDetachmentPoint
FixFieldSpec.Description: See DetachmentPoint(1458).

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoTargetPartyIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the number of target parties identified in a mass action.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TargetPartyID
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyID value within an target party repeating group.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TargetPartyIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyIDSource value within an target party repeating group.Same values as PartyIDSource (447) Valid values:For all PartyRoles B - BIC (Bank Identification Code - SWIFT managed) code (ISO9362 - See "Appendix 6-B") C - Generally accepted market participant identifier (e.g. NASD mnemonic) D - Proprietary / Custom code E - ISO Country Code F - Settlement Entity Location (note if Local Market Settlement use "E=ISO Country Code") (see "Appendix 6-G" for valid values) G - MIC (ISO 10383 - Market Identificer Code) (See "Appendix 6-C") H - CSD participant/member code (e.g.. Euroclear, DTC, CREST or Kassenverein number)For PartyRole = "InvestorID" and for CIV 6 - UK National Insurance or Pension Number 7 - US Social Security Number 8 - US Employer or Tax ID Number 9 - Australian Business Number A - Australian Tax File NumberFor PartyRole = "InvestorID" and for Equities 1 - Korean Investor ID 2 - Taiwanese Qualified Foreign Investor ID QFII/FID 3 - Taiwanese Trading Acct 4 - Malaysian Central Depository (MCD) number 5 - Chinese Investor IDFor PartyRole="Broker of Credit" I - Directed broker three character acronym as defined in ISITC "ETC Best Practice" guidelines document

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityListID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies an identifier for a Security List

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityListRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies a reference from one Security List to another. Used to support a hierarchy of Security Lists.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityListDesc
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies a description or name of a Security List.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedSecurityListDescLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedSecurityListDesc (tbd) field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedSecurityListDesc
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the SecurityListDesc (1467) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the SecurityListDesc field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityListType
FixFieldSpec.Description:
Specifies a type of Security List. Valid values: 1 - Industry Classification 2 - Trading List 3 - Market / Market Segment List 4 - Newspaper List
or any value conforming to the data type Reserved100Plus

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityListTypeSource
FixFieldSpec.Description:
Specifies a specific source for a SecurityListType. Relevant when a certain type can be provided from various sources. Valid values: 1 - ICB (Industry Classification Benchmark) published by Dow Jones and FTSE - www.icbenchmark.com 2 - NAICS (North American Industry Classification System). Replaced SIC (Standard Industry Classification) www.census.gov/naics or www.naics.com. 3 - GICS (Global Industry Classification Standard) published by Standards & Poor
or any value conforming to the data type Reserved100Plus

FixFieldSpec.Name: NewsID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for a News message

FixFieldSpec.Name: NewsCategory
FixFieldSpec.Description:
Category of news mesage. Valid values: 0 - Company News 1 - Marketplace News 2 - Financial Market News 3 - Technical News 99 - Other News
or any value conforming to the data type Reserved100Plus

FixFieldSpec.Name: LanguageCode
FixFieldSpec.Description: The national language in which the news item is provided.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoNewsRefIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of News reference items

FixFieldSpec.Name: NewsRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference to another News message identified by NewsID(1474).

FixFieldSpec.Name: NewsRefType
FixFieldSpec.Description:
Type of reference to another News Message item. Defines if the referenced news item is a replacement, is in a different language, or is complimentary. Valid values: 0 - Replacement 1 - Other Language 2 - Complimentary
or any value conforming to the data type Reserved100Plus

FixFieldSpec.Name: StrikePriceDeterminationMethod
FixFieldSpec.Description:
Specifies how the strike price is determined at the point of option exercise. The strike may be fixed throughout the life of the option, set at expiration to the value of the underlying, set to the average value of the underlying , or set to the optimal value of the underlying. Conditionally, required if value is other than "fixed". Valid values: 1 - Fixed Strike 2 - Strike set at expiration to underlying or other value (lookback floating) 3 - Strike set to average of underlying settlement price across the life of the option 4 - Strike set to optimal value
or any value conforming to the data type Reserved100Plus

FixFieldSpec.Name: StrikePriceBoundaryMethod
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the boundary condition to be used for the strike price relative to the underlying price at the point of option exercise. Valid values: 1 - Less than underlying price is in-the-money (ITM) 2 - Less than or equal to the underlying price is in-the-money(ITM) 3 - Equal to the underlying price is in-the-money(ITM) 4 - Greater than or equal to underlying price is in-the-money(ITM) 5 - Greater than underlying is in-the-money(ITM)

FixFieldSpec.Name: StrikePriceBoundaryPrecision
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used in combination with StrikePriceBoundaryMethod to specify the percentage of the strike price in relation to the underlying price. The percentage is generally 100 or greater for puts and 100 or less for calls.

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingPriceDeterminationMethod
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies how the underlying price is determined at the point of option exercise. The underlying price may be set to the current settlement price, set to a special reference, set to the optimal value of the underlying during the defined period ("Look-back") or set to the average value of the underlying during the defined period ("Asian option"). Valid values: 1 - Regular 2 - Special reference 3 - Optimal value (Lookback) 4 - Average value (Asian option)

FixFieldSpec.Name: OptPayoutType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the type of payout that will result from an in-the-money option. Valid values: 1 - Vanilla 2 - Capped 3 - Binary

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoComplexEvents
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of complex event occurrences.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ComplexEventType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type of complex event. Valid values: 1 - Capped 2 - Trigger 3 - Knock-in up 4 - Kock-in down 5 - Knock-out up 6 - Knock-out down 7 - Underlying 8 - Reset Barrier 9 - Rolling Barrier

FixFieldSpec.Name: ComplexOptPayoutAmount
FixFieldSpec.Description: Cash amount indicating the pay out associated with an event. For binary options this is a fixed amount.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ComplexEventPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the price at which the complex event takes effect. Impact of the event price is determined by the ComplexEventType(1484).

FixFieldSpec.Name: ComplexEventPriceBoundaryMethod
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the boundary condition to be used for the event price relative to the underlying price at the point the complex event outcome takes effect as determined by the ComplexEventPriceTimeType. Valid values: 1 - Less than ComplexEventPrice(1486) 2 - Less than or equal to ComplexEventPrice(1486) 3 - Equal to ComplexEventPrice(1486) 4 - Greater than or equal to ComplexEventPrice(1486) 5 - Greater than ComplexEventPrice(1486)

FixFieldSpec.Name: ComplexEventPriceBoundaryPrecision
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used in combination with ComplexEventPriceBoundaryMethod to specify the percentage of the strike price in relation to the underlying price. The percentage is generally 100 or greater for puts and 100 or less for calls.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ComplexEventPriceTimeType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies when the complex event outcome takes effect. The outcome of a complex event is a payout or barrier action as specified by the ComplexEventType. Valid values: 1 - Expiration 2 - Immediate (At Any Time) 3 - Specified Date/Time

FixFieldSpec.Name: ComplexEventCondition
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the condition between complex events when more than one event is specified. Multiple barrier events would use an "or" condition since only one can be effective at a given time. A set of digital range events would use an "and" condition since both conditions must be in effect for a payout to result. Valid values: 1 - And 2 - Or

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoComplexEventDates
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of complex event date occurrences for a given complex event.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ComplexEventStartDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the start date of the date range on which a complex event is effective. The start date will be set equal to the end date for single day events such as Bermuda optionsComplexEventStartDate must always be less than or equal to ComplexEventEndDate.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ComplexEventEndDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the end date of the date range on which a complex event is effective. The start date will be set equal to the end date for single day events such as Bermuda optionsComplexEventEndDate must always be greater than or equal to ComplexEventStartDate.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoComplexEventTimes
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of complex event time occurrences for a given complex event dateThe default in case of an absence of time fields is 00:00:00-23:59:59.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ComplexEventStartTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the start time of the time range on which a complex event date is effective. ComplexEventStartTime must always be less than or equal to ComplexEventEndTime.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ComplexEventEndTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the end time of the time range on which a complex event date is effective.ComplexEventEndTime must always be greater than or equal to ComplexEventStartTime.

FixFieldSpec.Name: StreamAsgnReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for the stream assignment request provided by the requester.

FixFieldSpec.Name: StreamAsgnReqType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of stream assignment request. Valid values: 1 - Stream assignment for new customer(s) 2 - Stream assignment for existing customer(s)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoAsgnReqs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of assignment requests.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDStreamID
FixFieldSpec.Description: The identifier or name of the price stream.

FixFieldSpec.Name: StreamAsgnRptID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier of the stream assignment report provided by the respondent.

FixFieldSpec.Name: StreamAsgnRejReason
FixFieldSpec.Description:
Reason code for stream assignment request reject. Valid values: 0 - Unknown client 1 - Exceeds maximum size 2 - Unknown or Invalid currency pair 3 - No available stream 99 - Other
or any value conforming to the data type Reserved100Plus

FixFieldSpec.Name: StreamAsgnAckType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of acknowledgement. Valid values: 0 - Assignment Accepted 1 - Assignment Rejected

FixFieldSpec.Name: RelSymTransactTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: See TransactTime(60)

FixFieldSpec.Name: StreamAsgnType
FixFieldSpec.Description: The type of assignment being affected in the Stream Assignment Report. Valid values: 1 - Assignment 2 - Rejected 3 - Terminate/Unassign
